  "text": "The crucial phase of the cell cycle before mitosis is the DNA replication during the S phase. Errors during the replication process itself may lead to misincorporation errors or stalled replication forks [CITATION_1] ). On the other hand, the most important repair mechanism during this phase of the cell cycle is homologous recombination, which allows precise repair (for review see [CITATION_2] . Several parallel pathways have been identified to delay the S phase.",
